k woman in Italy—Makaping describes acts of racist aggression that are wearying and degrading to encounter on a daily basis. She also offers her perspective on how various forms of inequality based on race, color, gender, and class feed off each other. Reversing the Gaze invites readers to confront the question of racism through the retelling of everyday occurrences that we might have experienced as victims, perpetrators, or witnesses.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aBamileke (African people)zItalyvBiography. 0aBlack peoplezItalyxSocial conditions. 0aCameroonianszItalyvBiography. 0aMarginality, SocialzItaly. 0aWomen immigrantszItalyvBiography. 0aWomen, BlackzItalyvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh  aanthropological memoir, Traiettorie di sguardi, Università della Calabria, Geneviève Makaping, racism, sexism, Italy, discrimination in Italy, author analysis, trips to italy, Italian scholars, Bamileke Immigrant Woman, Bamileke.1 aBellesia Contuzzi, Giovanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrioni, Simone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrioni, Simone, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aContuzzi, Giovanna Bellesia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoletto, Victoria Offredi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRomeo, Caterina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079130340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197883472940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978834729423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978834729/original  a978-3-11-079130-3  Rutgers Univer